This is an incredibly unique and visionary open-source project. By mapping the binary and structural rules of Telugu Chandassu (prosody) and Kirtanas, you are essentially building a Linguistic Compiler and Structural Evaluator for Telugu AI.
Here is your comprehensive, step-by-step blueprint to launch this on GitHub.
------------------------------
## 📛 Project Name Suggestions
Choose a name that reflects the bridge between ancient Telugu poetic structure and modern computational science:

   1. chandas-compile (Simple, clear, and highly searchable for open-source devs).
   2. padya-matrix (Sounds modern; reflects the mathematical grid nature of Ganamulu).
   3. annama-fsm (If you want to focus heavily on the Finite State Machine structure of Kirtanas).
   4. telugu-prosody-ai (Great for academic and AI community visibility).

Recommended Pick: chandas-compile (We will use this for the steps below).
------------------------------
